  (timeliness of submission) - Accuracy (closeness of the reported
  value to the underlying supervisory concept; absence of mistakes) -
  Completeness (availability of required information) - Reliability
  (closeness of revised values to the initially reported values;
  assessed via resubmission studies) - Plausibility (detection of
  outliers via time‑series review and peer comparisons)  Supervisory
  action a JST can take if a quarterly data quality report flags
