Question: We need to take an urgent supervisory decision against a bank to
  prevent damage to the financial system, but normal hearings and
  meeting timelines are too slow. What flexibility is available
  regarding the right to be heard and the non-objection procedure
  itself?
Example answer: In the case of an urgent decision necessary to prevent significant
  damage to the financial system, the ECB may adopt a supervisory
  decision adversely affecting the rights of the addressee without
  giving it the opportunity to comment beforehand; the hearing is then
  postponed and organised as soon as possible after adoption, with a
  clear justification provided in the decision. Under the emergency
  procedure for non-objection, deadlines for written procedures may be
  adjusted, a Supervisory Board meeting may be organised at short
  notice including by teleconference with a 50% quorum, and a shorter
  deadline may be requested of the Governing Council, which may even
  convene immediately after a Supervisory Board meeting. (ECB
  Supervisory Manual, pages 21, 24)
Predicted answer: (i) The right to be heard is preserved but may be curtailed in urgent
  cases: addressees are normally granted two weeks for comments
  (written procedures use five working days for comments/objections
  and the non‑objection procedure allows up to ten working days), but
  the hearing period can be shortened to a minimum of three working
  days or postponed entirely where the ECB adopts a decision without
  prior hearing to prevent significant damage, with a clear
  justification and the hearing organised as soon as possible
  thereafter; (ii) the non‑objection procedure can be accelerated in
  emergencies — deadlines may be shortened, Supervisory Board meetings
  may be convened at short notice (including by teleconference), the
  Supervisory Board may request a shorter Governing Council
  non‑objection deadline and the Governing Council may convene
  immediately — with specific quorum accommodations for emergency
  meetings. (ECB Supervisory Manual, pp. 21–22, 25)
